    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air, then boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>chicken breast strips</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-chicken-and-coconut-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat, once hot, add the<strong> chopped chicken</strong> and<strong> onion wedges </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until the chicken is starting to brown and the onion is starting to soften</p><p>Meanwhile cut your <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely, set some aside for garnish then, bash your <strong>lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, remove the <strong>tough outer layers</strong> of your lemongrass and discard, chop the <strong>softer inner core[s]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-chicken-and-coconut-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]<strong> </strong></span><strong>boiled water </strong>\u2014 this is your <strong>chicken stock</strong></p><p>Once the chicken has browned, add <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and your <strong>red Thai curry paste</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-chicken-and-coconut-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chicken stock</strong>,<strong> chopped lemongrass</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until the sauce has reduced and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-chicken-and-coconut-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [250ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-chicken-and-coconut-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, strip your <strong>coriander leaves </strong>from their stalks and chop the <strong>stalks</strong> finely, then chop the <strong>leaves</strong> finely and set aside for garnish</p><p>Crush your <strong>roasted peanuts </strong>with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Tip: If you don't have a rolling pin, just chop them roughly!</p><p>Chop your <strong>lime[s]</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-chicken-and-coconut-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, add the <strong>chopped coriander stalks</strong> to the pan</p><p>Add your <strong>cultured coconut</strong> and the juice of <strong>half</strong> the<strong> lime[s]</strong> to the pan \u2014 this is your <strong>Thai-style chicken & coconut curry</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into wedges</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-chicken-and-coconut-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Thai-style chicken & coconut curry</strong> with the<strong> cauliflower rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the<strong> chopped peanuts</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coriander leaves</strong>, <strong>remaining chopped chilli </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
